  "text": "Mass transport methods have been proposed to establish distance metrics between images [CITATION_1] and geometries [Lipman and Daubechies ] . For example, [CITATION_2] use the earth movers distance (EMD) between color histograms as a metric for image retrieval [CITATION_3] . For the task of 2D shapes interpolation, clustered mass transport has also been proposed [CITATION_4] , reconstructing binary silhouettes from the advected fuzzy clustering. In computer vision, mass transport has been used for visual tracking. In particular, [CITATION_5] specifically tailored a fast EMD computation for visual tracking, but results have only been demonstrated on 16 clusters while we handle thousands.",
